## Constructors in Python

In Python, a constructor is a special method used for initializing the attributes of a class when an object is created. Constructors are defined using the `__init__` method within a class.

### Syntax of a Constructor:

```python
class ClassName:
    def __init__(self, parameter1, parameter2, ...):
        # Constructor body
        # Initialize attributes using parameters



######################################################
Example:

class Car:
    def __init__(self, make, model, year):
        self.make = make
        self.model = model
        self.year = year

# Creating an instance of the Car class
my_car = Car(make="Toyota", model="Camry", year=2022)

# Accessing attributes using the instance
print("Make:", my_car.make)
print("Model:", my_car.model)
print("Year:", my_car.year)
